{
  "texts": [
    "To address the nonstandard task definitions common in previous benchmark suites (see §2: RELAT-EDWORK), FLAME uses a scenario-based taxonomy.",
    "Our taxonomy improves on prior works by defining the complex scenario space within FinNLP.",
    "Unlike prior works, the FLAME taxonomy categorizes financial data based on their primary characteristics and attributes.",
    "We define our taxonomy based on these characteristics to avoid creating superfluous categories that unnecessarily add complexity by diverging from established NLP terminology.",
    "Our taxonomy is intentionally designed to rely on broad categories (with subcategories as appropriate) to maintain a balance between simplicity and granularity."
  ]
}